---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Book a demo"
description: "Grade up to 10 of your roles, live. See the Engage methodology applied to your organisation in a 60–90 minute working session."
---
    <div class="page-hero">
<div class="page-hero-inner">
<div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span>Book a demo</div>
<div class="eyebrow">Experience the methodology</div>
<h1>Grade up to 10 roles.<br/><em>Live.</em></h1>
<p class="lead">The fastest way to understand Engage is not to read about it. It is to see it applied to your organisation. Book a session and we will evaluate a sample of your roles using the methodology — live, in context, with your structure.</p>
</div>
</div>
<section class="main-section">
<div class="main-inner">
<!-- LEFT COLUMN -->
<div>
{% if media.demoImage %}<img class="page-photo demo-image" src="{{ media.demoImage }}" alt="An Engage working session"/>{% else %}<div class="img-slot ratio-wide demo-image"><div class="img-slot-label"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.8"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg>Photo slot &middot; a working-session image</div></div>{% endif %}
<div class="expect-block">
<h2>What happens in the session</h2>
<p>This is not a generic presentation. It is a practical working session designed to give you a real view of how Engage works before any commitment is made.</p>
<div class="session-steps">
<div class="session-step">
<div class="step-num">1</div>
<div><strong>We review your roles</strong><span>A small sample of roles from your organisation — titles, reporting structure, and context. That is all we need to get started.</span></div>
</div>
<div class="session-step">
<div class="step-num">2</div>
<div><strong>We apply the Engage framework live</strong><span>Each role is evaluated across the five grids — Technical, Managerial, Persuasive, Control, and Impact — with the logic explained at every step.</span></div>
</div>
<div class="session-step">
<div class="step-num">3</div>
<div><strong>We show you how decisions are made</strong><span>No black box. Every judgement is visible. You will see exactly how the committee-based logic works in practice.</span></div>
</div>
<div class="session-step">
<div class="step-num">4</div>
<div><strong>We translate outputs into grades</strong><span>You see how the evaluation converts into grading outcomes — and how those can align to your existing structure or a new one.</span></div>
</div>
<div class="session-step">
<div class="step-num">5</div>
<div><strong>We discuss fit and next steps</strong><span>At the end of the session you will have a clear view of whether Engage is the right model for your organisation — and what a full implementation could look like.</span></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="prepare-box">
<h3>What to bring to the session</h3>
<ul class="prepare-list">
<li>5 to 10 role titles from your organisation</li>
<li>A basic reporting structure or organogram</li>
<li>Any current grading information, if available</li>
<li>A short explanation of your main grading challenge</li>
<li>Any specific concerns around fairness, consistency, or governance</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="leave-with">
<h3>What you leave with</h3>
<ul class="leave-list">
<li>A clear understanding of the Engage methodology in practice</li>
<li>Practical insight into how your roles may be evaluated</li>
<li>Greater confidence in the logic behind the framework</li>
<li>A view on whether Engage is right for your organisation</li>
<li>A clear next-step path if you decide to proceed</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="for-section">
<h2>Who this session is designed for</h2>
<div class="for-grid">
<div class="for-item">Organisations with 200+ employees or equivalent complexity</div>
<div class="for-item">HR or reward leaders rethinking their grading methodology</div>
<div class="for-item">Organisations looking for more transparency in job evaluation</div>
<div class="for-item">Businesses restructuring or growing rapidly</div>
<div class="for-item">Teams looking for a solution they can sustain internally</div>
<div class="for-item">Organisations operating across multiple countries or sites</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
