<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq-section">
<div class="faq-inner">
<h2>Common questions about the session</h2>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is this session free? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">Yes. The proof-of-concept session is offered to qualified organisations at no cost. It is designed to help you assess whether the Engage methodology is the right fit before making any commitment.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does the session take? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">Typically between 60 and 90 minutes, depending on the number of roles and the depth of discussion. We will confirm the exact format when we follow up on your booking.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can it be done online? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">Yes. Sessions can be conducted virtually via video call. In-person sessions are also available in South Africa and selected African markets. We will confirm the format based on your location.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do we need full job descriptions to participate? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">No. Job descriptions can be useful as a reference, but they are not required for the session. Engage is designed to work with direct role knowledge and structured discussion. A basic sense of the roles and reporting structure is enough to get started.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Who should attend from our side? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">Ideally someone with a good understanding of your organisation's structure and roles — typically an HR Director, Head of Reward, or equivalent. Having a business leader present can also be valuable if you want to test how the methodology reads across different role types.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What happens after the session? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></div>
<div class="faq-a">We will follow up with a summary of what was discussed and three options for how to proceed — licence only, full implementation support, or a hybrid model. There is no obligation to move forward, but if the session has been useful, the next step is usually a follow-up conversation to scope the right approach for your organisation.</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
